@node FDT_WhatIS "FinalDT Introduction"

  FinalDT  is  a  tool  which allows Final Writer users to load pictures inside
their documents using DataTypes.

  This  tool  opens  a large world to Final Writer, offering it a wide world of
pictures...   now you have no more limits:  GIFs, PCXs, JPEG and anything which
can be loaded by a DataType can be placed inside a document of yours!!!

  FinalDT is small, fast, robust and flexible.

  Have a nice time with it and Final Writer.
@endnode

@node FDT_Needs "FinalDT - Requirements"

    To use FinalDT you need:

    * An Amiga with OS3.0+ (for loading datatypes)

    * Final Writer V3.0+

    * Some dadatypes ;)


  If you have all of these things, well you are a good candidate for the use of
FinalDT.

@endnode

@node FDT_Install "FinalDT - Installation"

    The installation is a bit tricky... follow me.

    1 - Copy FinalDT program inside a directory you want (remeber the path
        because you will need it later)

    2 - Copy FinalDT.rexx inside FinalWriter/FWMacros directory.

    3 - Load a text editor (CED, ed and so on...) and load FinalDT.rexx 
        file in it.

    4 - Edit FinalDT.rexx file, changing JUST the path in which you have
        placed FinalDT program, and save the file again.

    - - At this point the installation is almost finished. 
        All you still have to do is to add FinalDT.rexx macro to a
        FinalWriter button or Menu item. 

        To do this, just have a look to your FinalWriter manual.

@endnode

@node FDT_HowToUse "FinalDT - How To Use"

    The use of FinalDT is very straightfoward:

    Call the FinalDT.rexx macro with the button or menu item you have
    configured, and a file requester will appear.

    Select the picture you want to load and ... wait for a while.

    The picture is placed on the screen.

    NOTE1: due to the fact that sometimes FianlWriter V3.0 sets a too
           big dimension to a picture, I have forced it to be 5.0, 5.0
           wide and tall. This is not a limitation: when a picture is
           loaded, hold down SHIFT and try to resize the picture: it
           will be set to its original proportions.

    NOTE2: Final Writer has some params that could be set to -1 for
           using defaults, unfortunately, this params seem not to
           work (I'll write a bug report to SoftWood as soon as I can)
           So I was forced to set picture's position X,Y to 2.0, 2.0.

           You can anyway drag the picture around the screen.

@endnode

